HEADWORD: Catalectic
<hw>Cat`a*lec"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>catalecticus</ets>, Gr. <?/ incomplete, fr. <?/ to leave off;
<grk>kata`</grk> down, wholly + <grk>lh`gein</grk> to stop.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Pros.)</fld> <def>Wanting a syllable at the end, or
terminating in an imperfect foot; <as>as, a <ex>catalectic</ex>
verse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Photog. & Chem.)</fld> <def>Incomplete; partial;
not affecting the whole of a substance.</def>
<rj><au>Abney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

